<h3 id="doc-disabled-state">Disabled State</h3>
<p>Use the <code>disabled</code> attribute to visually indicate that a
field is not editable. Disabled inputs appear dimmed and use alternate
border and placeholder colors based on the theme.</p>
<div
class="w-max-md mt-4 card p-3 border dark:border-grey-900 light:border-grey-100">
<p><input class="form-control" disabled placeholder="Disabled input"></p>
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;input class=&quot;form-control&quot; disabled placeholder=&quot;Disabled input&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
<h3 id="doc-validation-states">Validation States</h3>
<p>Add <code>.valid</code> or <code>.invalid</code> classes to style
form fields based on validation.</p>
<div
class="w-max-md mt-4 card p-3 border dark:border-grey-900 light:border-grey-100">
<p><input class="mb-4 form-control valid" placeholder="Valid input">
<input class="form-control invalid" placeholder="Invalid input"></p>
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;input class=&quot;form-control valid&quot; placeholder=&quot;Valid input&quot;&gt;
&lt;input class=&quot;form-control invalid&quot; placeholder=&quot;Invalid input&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
<h3 id="doc-rounded-pill">Rounded Pill</h3>
<p>To give inputs a pill-shaped appearance, add the
<code>.rounded-pill</code> class. This applies a large border-radius to
create fully rounded edges.</p>
<div
class="w-max-md mt-4 card p-3 border dark:border-grey-900 light:border-grey-100">
<p><input class="form-control rounded-pill" placeholder="Rounded Pill Input"></p>
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;input class=&quot;form-control rounded-pill&quot; placeholder=&quot;Rounded Pill Input&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
<h3 id="doc-without-border">Without Border</h3>
<p>Use the <code>.border-0</code> utility to remove borders from form
controls when a minimal or embedded style is desired.</p>
<div
class="w-max-md mt-4 card p-3 border dark:border-grey-900 light:border-grey-100">
<p><input class="form-control border-0" placeholder="Input without borders"></p>
</div>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;input class=&quot;form-control border-0&quot; disabled placeholder=&quot;Input without borders&quot;&gt;</code></pre>
